    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      644.48,
      527.15,
      658.48
    ],
    "text": "application of the sudden fight. On perusal of the evidence led before the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      665.6,
      527.22,
      679.6
    ],
    "text": "High Court, although evidence of sudden fight was elicited from the evidence",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      686.72,
      527.19,
      700.72
    ],
    "text": "of the prosecution, the same was not suggested during the cross",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      707.84,
      527.02,
      721.84
    ],
    "text": "examination. According to Section 105 of the Evidence Ordinance, it is the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 3,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      728.98,
      527.04,
      742.98
    ],
    "text": "responsibility of the Appellant to prove the existence of a general or special",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      265.61,
      35.25,
      337.69,
      45.8
    ],
    "text": "CA/HCC/0157/22",
    "fonts": [
      "Cambria"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      474.22,
      758.04,
      525.94,
      769.08
    ],
    "text": "5 | P a g e",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      88.32,
      527.03,
      102.32
    ],
    "text": "exception during the trial on a balance of probabilities. In the absence of",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      109.56,
      527.04,
      123.56
    ],
    "text": "such proof, the Learned Trial Judge should direct his mind to the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      130.68,
      527.03,
      144.68
    ],
    "text": "circumstances and the fact that the Appellant is entitled to have the benefit",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      151.8,
      199.97,
      165.8
    ],
    "text": "of the lesser verdict.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      182.88,
      514.44,
      196.88
    ],
    "text": "In The King v Bellana Vithanage Eddin 41 NLR 345 the court held that:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      214.08,
      526.64,
      228.14
    ],
    "text": "\"In a charge of murder, it is the duty of the judge to put to the jury the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      235.23,
      526.68,
      249.29
    ],
    "text": "alternative of finding the accused guilty of culpable homicide not",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      256.35,
      526.69,
      270.41
    ],
    "text": "amounting to murder when there is any basis for such a finding in the",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      277.47,
      526.92,
      291.53
    ],
    "text": "evidence on record, although such defence was not raised nor relied upon",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      298.59,
      202.13,
      312.65
    ],
    "text": "by the accused\u201d.",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      329.67,
      465.94,
      343.67
    ],
    "text": "In the case of King v. Albert Appuhamy 40 NLR 505 it was held:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      360.87,
      526.82,
      374.93
    ],
    "text": "\u201cFailure on the part of a prisoner or his Counsel to take up a certain line of",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      381.99,
      526.81,
      396.05
    ],
    "text": "defence does not relieve a Judge of the responsibility of putting to the jury",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      403.13,
      340.63,
      417.19
    ],
    "text": "such defence if it arises on the evidence.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      434.21,
      473.62,
      448.21
    ],
    "text": "In the case of King v. Withanalage Lanty 42 NLR 317 it was held:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      465.41,
      526.88,
      479.47
    ],
    "text": "\u201cThere was evidence in this case upon which it was open to the jury to say",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle",
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      486.53,
      526.61,
      500.59
    ],
    "text": "that it came within exception 4 to section 294 of the Penal Code and that",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      507.65,
      526.82,
      521.71
    ],
    "text": "the appellant was guilty of culpable homicide not amounting to murder. No",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      528.77,
      526.85,
      542.83
    ],
    "text": "such plea, however, was put forward on his behalf. In the course of his",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      549.89,
      526.8,
      563.95
    ],
    "text": "charge the presiding Judge referred to this evidence as part of the defence",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      571.04,
      526.67,
      585.1
    ],
    "text": "story but not as evidence upon which a lesser verdict might possibly be",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      592.16,
      527.03,
      606.22
    ],
    "text": "based. Held, that it was the duty of the presiding Judge to have so directed",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      613.28,
      526.68,
      627.34
    ],
    "text": "the jury and that in the circumstances the appellant was entitled to have",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      99.38,
      634.4,
      288.31,
      648.46
    ],
    "text": "the benefit of the lesser verdict.\u201d",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Italic"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      665.6,
      389.86,
      679.58
    ],
    "text": "Section 297 of the Penal Code states as follows:",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle-Bold"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      696.68,
      527.06,
      710.68
    ],
    "text": "Whoever commits culpable homicide not amounting to murder shall be",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      717.8,
      527.06,
      731.8
    ],
    "text": "punished with imprisonment of either description for a term which may",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 4,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      738.94,
      527.0,
      752.94
    ],
    "text": "extend to twenty years, and shall also be liable to fine, if the act by which",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      265.61,
      35.25,
      337.69,
      45.8
    ],
    "text": "CA/HCC/0157/22",
    "fonts": [
      "Cambria"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      9.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      474.22,
      758.04,
      525.94,
      769.08
    ],
    "text": "6 | P a g e",
    "fonts": [
      "Calibri"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      11.039999961853027
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      88.32,
      527.15,
      102.32
    ],
    "text": "the death is caused is done with the intention of causing death, or of causing",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      109.56,
      527.18,
      123.56
    ],
    "text": "such bodily injury as is likely to cause death; or with imprisonment of either",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      130.68,
      527.2,
      144.68
    ],
    "text": "description for a term which may extend to ten years, or with fine, or with",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      151.8,
      526.99,
      165.8
    ],
    "text": "both, if the act is done with the knowledge that it is likely to cause death,",
    "fonts": [
      "BookmanOldStyle"
    ],
    "sizes": [
      12.0
    ]
  },
  {
    "page_number": 5,
    "bbox": [
      78.02,
      172.92,
      527.03,
